==== Follow the guidelines ====
Please see <nowiki>[[https://wiki.ubuntu.com/UbuntuGNOME/Artwork/Trusty/CommunityWallpapers|Community Wallpapers]]</nowiki> for submission guidelines.

Submissions ''must'' adhere to the <nowiki>[[http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0|Creative Commons ShareAlike 4.0]]</nowiki> (CC-BY-SA 4.0) license to be considered for use in Ubuntu GNOME. Please always specify this license with your submission; this confirms us you are willing to share your submission with that license, have understood the license terms and that it is your work (or correctly attributed).

Attached files that are not added to the wiki page (relatively shortly) and thus/or have no author and/or license mentioned will be removed. (Note to submitters: You can check the <nowiki>[[https://wiki.ubuntu.com/UbuntuGNOME/Artwork/Trusty/CommunityWallpapers?action=info|history page]]</nowiki> of the wiki to see why your submission was removed.)

The last date of submission is February 27th.

==== How to submit ====
If you're not sure how this page works and if you're running into trouble, please <nowiki>[[https://wiki.ubuntu.com/UbuntuGNOME/Artwork/Trusty/CommunityWallpapers/HowTo|go to this place for instructions on how to submit]]</nowiki> your artwork.

You can also use the <nowiki>[[http://www.flickr.com/groups/2484760@N20/|Flickr page]]</nowiki> if you don't want to use the wiki.

==== Accepted submissions ====
All the submissions that don't fulfill the guidelines will be removed from the page.
